Line 1. Total wages, salaries, tips, unemployment compensation, etc.
Line 2. Taxable interest and ordinary dividends. (If more than $1500, file Form D-40.)
Line 4. Standard deduction plus exemption. If single, enter $5775. If filing jointly, enter $7450, or if claimed as a dependent on another's tax return, enter $4100.
Line 6. Tax. Use the tax tables on pages 53-62 to find the tax on the Line 5 amount.
Line 7a. Enter number of exemptions claimed on your federal return.
Line 9a. Contribution to Public Fund for Drug Prevention and Children at Risk.
Line 9b. Contribution to DC Statehood Delegation Fund.
Line 9c. Contributions to Anacostia River Cleanup and Protection Fund.
Line 11. Total DC income tax withheld shown on Forms W-2 and 1099.
Line 12. Tax paid with extension of time to file or with original return if this is an amended return.
Line 13. DC Earned Income Tax Credit. Enter your federal earned income credit. Use Calc. LIC/EITC to see if EITC is greater. Leave blank if you took Line 7 LIC credit.
Line 13a. Enter number of qualified EITC children.
